  "prompt": "Someone deleted me on snapchat, so I deleted him & now he appears in my Added me section, but I cannot see his score. Does this mean he added me back?",
  "response": "When someone appears in your \"Added Me\" section on Snapchat, it typically means that they have added you as a friend. However, if you cannot see their Snapchat score, it could be due to a few reasons:\n\n1. **They Added You Back:** If the person re-added you after you both deleted each other, they would appear in your \"Added Me\" section. However, if you haven't accepted their friend request yet, you won't be able to see their Snapchat score.\n\n2. **Privacy Settings:** The person might have adjusted their privacy settings to hide their Snapchat score from non-friends or new friends. If you haven't re-added them as a friend, you wouldn't be able to see their score.\n\n3. **Technical Glitch:** Sometimes, Snapchat might experience technical issues that could affect the visibility of a user's score or cause delays in updating friend statuses.\n\nTo confirm if he added you back and to see his score, you can try re-adding him as a friend. If he has indeed added you back, his score should become visible once your friend request is accepted. If you're still unable to see his score after re-adding each other, it's likely due to his privacy settings.",
